[Event "Baker Bridge - Strong 2C Bids"]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "N:AQJ83.3.KQ7.AKQ9 T42.A9.AT653.542 K65.T864.92.T873 97.KQJ752.J84.J6"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
2C pass 2D pass 2S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: N, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 2, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/strong_2c"]
[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

With 22 points you should open 2\C. Partner responds 2\D.  

You have 22 points and 5-card Major suit. Your rebid is therefore 2\S. Partner raises to 4\S. His jump to game shows a weaker hand than a 3\S bid would so you pass.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:AQ.AK75.Q84.AKJT J62.82.J9632.Q54 K875.QJT3.T5.973 T943.964.AK7.862"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
2C pass 2D pass 2NT pass 3C pass 3H pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/strong_2c"]
[Student "S"]
{You have 6 points and bid a Negative 2\D. Partner now bids 2NT. What is your bid? 

Partner has a balanced 22-24 points. With your 6 you want to be in game, but which game; 3NT, 4\H or 4\S? You can't answer that question unless you know if partner has a 4-card Major suit. So you bid 3\C, which is Stayman in this case. Partner replies 3\H.  

Knowing of the 4-4 fit you bid 4\H. By the way: Partner knew your 3\C bid was not the Second Negative because you don't use Second Negative following a 2NT rebid, you just pass.}

