[Deal "N:AK.KQJT4.AJT.KJ9 Q852.A7.Q74.T764 J943.96.9863.A82 T76.8532.K52.Q53"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
2C pass 2D pass 2H pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/strong_2c"]
[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

With 23 points you open 2\C. Partner responds 2\D.  

You bid your 5-card \H suit. Partner says 2NT.  

Partner's 2NT shows scattered values and fewer than 3 \Hs. He has 3 or more points or he would have bid the Double Negative. So you say 3NT.}

